What you need to know:  But even as fans troop to Muthaiga, some have close to zero plans of cheering on Kenyan players — they will certainly be hooked to what will be happening around the eventThis will be the first major sports event under the Kenya Kwanza regime, and Sports Cabinet Secretary Ababu Namwamba will be keen to ensure organisers sell Kenya as a prime sports tourism destination in line with the “Talanta Hela” programmeIt will also be a big opportunity for other sports federations to learn from golf and match the standards set by Kenya Open Golf Limited Tournament Director Patrick Obath and his team